  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ertaining to the spiritual life are ordained to this union, as to their end. Hence the Apostle says ( 1 Timothy 1:5 ): "The end of the commandment is charity from a pure heart, and a good conscience , and an unfeigned faith ." For all the virtues , about whose acts the precepts are given, are directed either to the | love to the thing beloved, as shown above ( II-II:25:12 ; II-II:26:1 and II-II:26:2 ). It is therefore evident that the order of charity must come under the precept.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.charity" target="concept.will" id="edge.concept.charity.resides_in.concept.will">
