  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q010.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">so that a man be called an unbeliever, merely because he has not the faith . Secondly, unbelief may be taken by way of opposition to the faith ; in which sense a man refuses to hear the faith , or despises it, according to Isaiah 53:1 : "Who hath believed our report?" It is this that completes the not</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
