<edge source="concept.virtue" target="concept.charity" id="edge.concept.virtue.perfected_by.concept.charity">
  <data key="d6">edge.concept.virtue.perfected_by.concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.virtue</data>
  <data key="d8">Virtue</data>
  <data key="d9">virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">perfected_by</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d12">Charity</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-virtue-perfected-by-concept-charity-st-ii-ii-q023-a008-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Now it is evident, in accordance with what has been said ( Article 7 ), that it is charity which directs the acts of all other virtues to the last end, and which, consequently, also gives the form to all other acts of virtue : and it is precisely in this sense that charity is called the form of the virtues , for these are called virtues in relation to "informed" acts.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.wisdom_gift" target="concept.charity" id="edge.concept.wisdom_gift.caused_by.concept.charity">
  <data key="d6">edge.concept.wisdom_gift.caused_by.concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.wisdom_gift</data>
  <data key="d8">Gift of Wisdom</data>
  <data key="d9">gift_holy_spirit</data>
  <data key="d10">caused_by</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d12">Charity</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-wisdom-gift-caused-by-concept-charity-st-ii-ii-q045-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q045.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">which unites us to God , according to 1 Corinthians 6:17 : "He who is joined to the Lord, is one spirit." Consequently wisdom which is a gift , has its cause in the will , which cause is charity , but it has its essence in the intellect , whose act is to judge aright, as stated above ( I-II:14:1 ).</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
